Don't arrive too early - annoying preshow audio.
I could have sworn I had already posted my review of this place but apparently not.

Finally saw Myst√®re by Cirque du Soleil. I've seen all of the Cirque shows in Vegas except O.

Our seats were in the center in the lower level. The seats slightly recline when you lean back into them. There is a decent amount of space between rows. My husband got a great deal ($63-ish / ticket) so keep your eyes peeled for periodic specials.

This show relies heavily on acrobatics while the filler scenes between sets is baby / toddler-themed play. Not my cup of tea, but also not the end of the world.

The show is fine but I suggest showing up at the very last minute, otherwise you'll have to listen to audio of a grunting and rooting baby on loop before the show begins.

As far as Cirque shows, my favorite is still K√† because it has a storyline rather than simply acrobatics and stunts that are featured at multiple other Vegas shows.
